comment: Lee (CHA) maintains a legal guarding position as he defends Wade's (MIA) drive and jump shot attempt. Wade initiates contact on the play.
Wade (MIA) moves his pivot foot after ending his dribble. The official is looking for any potential illegal contact and does not pick up the pivot foot.
Williams (CHA) firms up as he sets the screen on Richardson (MIA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
RHH and L-SLA show that Whiteside (MIA) makes contact with Jefferson's (CHA) arm that affects his shot attempt.
Whiteside (MIA) makes incidental contact with Williams (CHA) after setting the screen.
Lin (CHA) makes contact with Deng's (MIA) arm that affects his ability to retrieve the rebound.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that possession belonged to Charlotte was upheld.
Whiteside (MIA) makes incidental contact with Zeller (CHA) away from the ball.
Zeller (CHA) sets the screen on Richardson (MIA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Zeller (CHA) sets the screen on Wade (MIA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Lee (CHA) establishes his left foot as his pivot after he gathers the ball and is permitted one more step.
Whiteside (MIA) hip checks Zeller (CHA) affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Williams (CHA) makes contact with Whiteside's (MIA) arm that affects his layup attempt.
Zeller (CHA) sets the screen on Richardson (MIA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Richardson (MIA) legally contests Walker's (CHA) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Deng (MIA) makes contact with Lee's (CHA) arm, affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
